workouts.title: Kickboxing, Kettlebell, and Core
workouts.training-type: Cardiovascular, Kettlebell, Strength Training, Toning, Kickboxing
workouts.details: This routine has a little bit of everything, which makes it very fun and goes by very quickly. In just over 30 minutes, you get a warm-up, cool-down, and 4 combo groups of sweaty, challenging goodness in between. So if you like kickboxing, you are going to like this routine; if you like kettlebells, you are going to like this routine; if you like core, then you will like this routine; and if you like all three, then, well, this may just be your dream workout.

workouts.title: Beginner-Friendly Cardio Warm Up
workouts.training-type: Cardiovascular, Low Impact, Warm Up/Cool Down
workouts.details: This low impact cardio workout makes a great warm up leading into a more intense workout, and it also makes a great short standalone workout. The light total body cardio intervals get the blood flowing and the muscles warmed up and ready for more intense work.

workouts.title: Restorative Bodyweight Workout
workouts.sub-title: Low Impact Exercises for Sore Muscles
workouts.training-type: Low Impact, Warm Up/Cool Down, Stretching/Flexibility
workouts.details: Is today a day you want to get moving but have a case of delayed onset muscle soreness (DOMS)? Or maybe you’re simply in the mood for some low-key and feel-good movement? This routine is the perfect way to accomplish either of those goals.

workouts.title: Single Weight Upper Body
workouts.details: Target the major muscles of the upper body using one weight at a time in this short, single circuit routine. You’re only completing the five-exercise circuit twice so challenge yourself to lift heavy (for you) while paying close attention to muscular imbalances and compensations that often occur with unilateral work. Remember that performance differences between the right and left side of the body are usually not solely derived from strength deficiencies but are also related to inefficient patterns of daily movement done with high repetition.

workouts.title: Pilates With Cardio Intermissions
workouts.sub-title: Lower Body Strength, Stability, and Cardio
workouts.details: This routine is a combination of Pilates and cardio. At 40-minutes long with no repeated exercises, you'll break a sweat and have some fun with this lower-body-focused routine.

workouts.title: Intermediate Power Yoga With Twists
workouts.details: Explore a balance of ground and water as we twist and unravel our way through a free-flowing sequence that will challenge your strength, balance, mobility, and proprioception.

workouts.title: Quick HIIT With Extended Cool Down
workouts.sub-title: Tabata-Inspired Intervals and Feel-Good Foam Rolling
workouts.details: Don’t let a busy schedule hold you back from getting in an awesome workout. This HIIT workout features Tabata-style circuits with quick rest breaks — all under 30 minutes.

workouts.title: Lower Body Strength
workouts.sub-title: Weighted Circuits with Bodyweight Tempo Training
workouts.details: This “leg day” routine includes plenty of squat, lunge, and deadlift variations for a comprehensive lower body workout. Slow down the tempo with the bodyweight intermissions — take a quick grip break before picking up your weights again!
